-- An open conjecture: double-negation elimination (~~P => P).
--
-- This is exactly the law that separates classical from intuitionistic logic.
-- It is NOT provable in our constructive kernel, so we do not prove it -- we
-- assume it as a `realistic` truth. Anything that leans on it is therefore
-- PROVEN *conditionally*, and the project report tracks that dependency.
conjecture dne :
  forall (P : Type), Imp (Not (Not P)) P
